definitions.definition: A person who plays the piano , particularly with skill or as part of an orchestra .
examples: By the time she became the world's greatest pianist , she had already practised for thousands of hours on her prized piano.

definitions.definition: A spy using radio or wireless telegraphy to keep in touch with headquarters during the Second World War .

main_definition: ( music ) A person who plays the piano , particularly with skill or as part of an orchestra .
secondary_definitions: ( WWII ) A spy using radio or wireless telegraphy to keep in touch with headquarters during the Second World War .
